A look at the upcoming weekend around the Big 12 Conference:GAME OF THE WEEKENDNo. 20 Texas at No. 10 Baylor, Saturday. The winner stays in the thick of the Big 12 race with Kansas. The Longhorns (18-6, 7-4 Big 12) are hot, having won five of six after their hard-earned 79-76 victory over the Jayhawks on Monday. They’re playing their fifth straight game against a ranked opponent. Baylor (20-4, 8-3) bounced back from a 24-point loss at Kansas a week ago with a 75-60 win at Kansas State on Wednesday. The injury bug has bitten Baylor in recent weeks. Season scoring leader LJ Cryer has missed four straight games with a foot injury. Baylor has won 10 of 11 against Texas.ADVERTISEMENTLOOKING AHEADTCU (16-5, 5-4) has a big opportunity to enhance its NCAA Tournament resume when it visits No. 9 Texas Tech on Saturday. The Horned Frogs get back 15-point-per-game scorer Mike Miles, who has missed two with a wrist injury. The Red Raiders (18-6, 7-4) are coming off a 70-55 loss at Oklahoma, ending a three-game win streak. TCU is 4-1 on the road this season but hasn’t won in Lubbock since 2015. SportsDoping hearing to decide Russian skater's Olympic fate Why has the 'Rooney Rule' not produced more Black coaches?Black NFL coaches lament hiring policies that fall shortPro Picks: All-in Rams or who'd-have-believed-it Bengals?The other game involving a ranked team has Oklahoma (14-10, 4-7) at No. 8 Kansas (19-4, 8-2). Last month the Sooners pushed KU before losing 67-64.PLAYER TO WATCHWest Virginia’s Taz Sherman came back from a concussion to turn in one of his best games of the season in a 79-63 win over Iowa State on Tuesday. Sherman scored a team-high 16 points, grabbed eight rebounds and handed out six assists. The Mountaineers play on the road Saturday at Oklahoma State, a team they beat 70-60 last month. In that game, Sherman had 13 points to go with four steals and five assists.INSIDE THE NUMBERSTwelve of the 16 players on Kansas State’s roster have combined to miss 79 games. Mark Smith is the only player to start all 23 games as injuries and COVID-19 protocols have forced head coach Bruce Weber to use 10 different starting lineups. ... Texas has posted a 48-8 advantage in points off turnovers against its last two opponents. The Longhorns tallied a 24-2 margin last Saturday against Iowa State and a 24-6 edge on Monday against Kansas. ... Iowa State’s Izaiah Brockington is on pace to become the first Cyclone to average 16 points and eight rebounds per game since Melvin Ejim in 2013-14. ON THE WOMEN’S SIDENo. 12 Oklahoma hosts No. 16 Texas on Saturday in the game of the weekend. The Sooners (20-3, 9-2) are on a four-game winning streak featuring two top-10 wins, including 65-63 over the then-No. 9 Longhorns on Jan. 29. Texas (16-6, 6-5) is coming off a win at Texas Tech that ended a three-game losing streak. ... Kansas (16-5, 7-4) has won four straight Big 12 games for the first time since 2009 and goes for five in a row Saturday when Kansas State (17-7, 7-5). The Jayhawks lost 69-61 at K-State on Jan. 19. The Jayhawks again must contend with national player of the year candidate or Ayoka Lee, who is third in the country at 24 points per game. Lee had 25 points and 15 rebounds the first time the teams met this season. ... No. 9 Iowa State (20-3, 9-2), which shares the Big 12 lead with Oklahoma, visits TCU (6-14, 2-9).___More AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and https://twitter.com/AP_Top25